						<summary>

						<p>On two stones built into the floor of the mosque in the village.</p>						

						<p>Eastern Chāḷukya: Sarvalōkāśraya Vishṇuvardhana.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of 4 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp; the gift was entrusted to Chellaṇḍu Peddibōya. Mentions Sakaṭamantani-nāḍu. In characters of 8th-9th century A.D.</p>						

